系統識別號
U0026-2608201316520800


論文名稱(中文) 
      
以臺灣地震損失評估系統強化臺南市震災應變機製作業之研究



論文名稱(英文) 
      
Strengthening Earthquake Disasters Prevention and Rescue Operations in Tainan City by Applying TELES


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
地球科學系專班


系所名稱(英)
Department of Earth Sciences (on the job class)


學年度
101


學期
2


出版年
102


研究生(中文)
向旭彬


學號
L47001063


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2013-07-30


論文頁數
77頁


口試委員
口試委員-丁澈士
口試委員-景國恩
指導教授-樂鍇．祿璞崚岸



關鍵字(中)
臺灣地震損失評估系統防災地震災害


關鍵字(英)
Taiwan Earthquake Loss Estimation SystemDisasters PreventionEarthquake Disasters


學科別分類



中文摘要
臺灣位處環太平洋地震帶上，生活在臺灣的我們隨時隨地皆處在地震災害的威脅，但何時要地震，何時會地震，以目前的科技而言，尚無法預知！有鑑於此，當務之急是必須在災前即做好防救災應變規劃，強化震災應變機制，以應不可知的震災突然發生時，能有效減少災害發生時的人命傷亡與財產損失。本研究利用國家地震工程研究中心開發的「臺灣地震損失評估系統-TELES」，選定由西元1736年、1946年分別發生過歷史地震事件並造成人命傷亡與大規模建築物毀損的新化斷層為研究區域，假設2個不同的芮氏地震規模（6.1及6.5），再使用TELES系統來推估模擬震災發生時的臺南市災害境況。經由TELEE系統模擬推估若在新化地震發生的區域再度發生地震時，可得知以下結果：建築物毀損較嚴重的區域多半集中在臺南市永康區、東區、新化區、歸仁區、仁德區、安南區、北區、新市區、中西區及南區；人員傷亡較嚴重的區域多半集中在臺南市永康區、東區、北區、新化區、中西區、安南區及仁德區；推論其原因很有可能是因為這些區域除了鄰近新化斷層外，大部份也位處於普通、軟弱的地盤上，且人口分佈與建築物密度也都較其它區域為高，故地震發生時勢必造成大規模的建築物毀損與人命傷亡。綜上所述，經由國家地震工程硏究中心開發的TELES系統，可用來模擬震災發生時可能造成的災損境況，應用在各縣市的震災境況及災損推估，據以強化震災應變機制，TELES系統產出研究結果亦可供中央或地方政府做為擬訂地區性災害防救計畫之參考。


英文摘要
Since Taiwan is located at the circum-Pacific seismic zone, people in Taiwan face the threat of massive disasters and destructions caused by earthquakes all the time. Though earthquakes cannot be predicted exactly at present, the huge property damage and loss of life by earthquakes can be reduced with emergency preparedness planning and effective rescue operations. In this study, “Taiwan Earthquake Loss Estimation System (TELES)” which is developed by National Center for Research on Earthquake Engineering (NCREE), was used in this study to analyze the damage patterns in Tainan City caused by the Hsinhua Fault. In the recent history, the Hsinhua Fault ruptured in 1736 and 1946(ML=6.1). In this study, we assumed two different earthquake events for Richter Magnitude Scale 6.1, and 6.5 to stimulate the earthquake disasters. Our study reveals that if an earthquake occurs in Hsinhua Fault again, the buildings may be destroyed seriously in the area of Yongkang district, East district, Xinhua district, Guiren district, Rende district, Annan district, North district, Xinshi district, West Central district and South district. Besides, lots of people may be injured or killed by the earthquake, mainly in the area of Yongkang district, East district, North district, Xinhua district, West Central district, Annan district and Rende district. These results can be explained that because these districts are closed to Hsinhua Fault zone and these districts have a high population density and the expansion of buildings. Moreover, the ground under these areas is quite soft, and this situation may amplify ground shaking. To sum up, these findings reported in this study have demonstrated that TELES can be practically used for earthquake disasters prevention or rescue operating system of the local or central governments. 


